body:
Hm, it now also fails in other plugin tests
https://travis-ci.org/dereuromark/cakephp-tools/jobs/622597363

All it uses is
```php
Router::scope('/', function (RouteBuilder $routes) {
	$routes->fallbacks(DashedRoute::class);
});
```

which worked fine since Cake 3.0.

Aha, so

    ->Url->build(['action' => 'x']);

was valid before (<= 3.8.6) and became `/x` URL (empty controller was removed).

Now in 3.8.7 this keeps the empty placeholders, in this case {controller}

Is this intended?
